man-3_printf 06 AUGUST 2022 "0x11.c printf by ALX SE Student "(MANUAL PAGE)

A.
NAME
.printf() - used to display the output on the console screen according to the format
 
B.
SYNOPSIS
.#include "main.h"
. int _printf(const char *format, ...);

C.
DESCRIPTION
.The printf() family of functions produces output according to a format

.Format of the format string - a character string, beginning and ending in
its initial shift state, if any.The format string is composedof zero or more directives
ordinary characters (not %), which are copied unchanged to the output stream; and conversion
specifications, each of which results in fetching zero or more subsequent arguments. Each conversion specification is
introduced by the character %, and ends with a conversion specifier.

.write output to stdout, the standard output stream

.RETURN VALUE - after successful return value the number of characters printed (excluding the null byte used to end output to strings)

.If an output error is encountered, a negative value is returned.

D.conversion specifiers:
 %c - Character Format Specifier
 %s -String Format Specifier
 % - start of format specifier symbol

E.
EXAMPLE
Write program function to printf name and color
#include 'main.h"
#include <stdio.h>

/**
 * printf - print name and color
 *
 * Return: 0
 */
int main(void)
{
  char name = MICKY;
  char color = "Blue";

printf("My name is %c\n", name);
printf("my favourite colour is %s", color);
return (0);
}

